%N A052036 Smallest number that must be added to n to make or keep n palindromic.
%H A052036 Patrick De Geest, <a href="https://www.worldofnumbers.com/index.html">World!Of Numbers</a>
%F A052036 a(n)=0 iff n is in A002113, otherwise a(n)=A052037(n)-1. - _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 26 2014
%e A052036 If n = 13 we need to add 9 to arrive at palindrome 22.
%t A052036 snpal[n_]:=Module[{k=0,idn},While[idn=IntegerDigits[n+k];idn != Reverse[ idn],k++];k]; Array[snpal,100,0] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Nov 27 2012 *)
%o A052036 (PARI) a(n)=for(k=0, 9e19, is_A002113(n+k)&&return(k)) \\ For illustrative purpose only, inefficient for most large numbers. - _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 26 2014
%o A052036 (Python)
%o A052036 def A052036(n):
%o A052036     sl = len(str(n))
%o A052036     l, w = divmod(sl,2)
%o A052036     l10 = 10**l
%o A052036     if w:
%o A052036         x = l+1
%o A052036         t = 10**(x-1)
%o A052036         t2 = t*10
%o A052036         for y in range(n//l10,t2):
%o A052036             k, m = y//10, 0
%o A052036             while k >= 10:
%o A052036                 k, r = divmod(k,10)
%o A052036                 m = 10*m + r
%o A052036             z = y*t + 10*m + k
%o A052036             if z >= n:
%o A052036                 return z-n
%o A052036     else:
%o A052036         x = l
%o A052036         t = 10**(x-1)
%o A052036         t2 = t*10
%o A052036         for y in range(n//l10,t2):
%o A052036             k, m = y, 0
%o A052036             while k >= 10:
%o A052036                 k, r = divmod(k,10)
%o A052036                 m = 10*m + r
%o A052036             z = y*t2 + 10*m + k
%o A052036             if z >= n:
%o A052036                 return z-n # _Chai Wah Wu_, Feb 05 2026
